OL,6,FThe weekday programmes had, by then,
OL,7,Fstarted to gain their own visual
OL,8,Fidentities, computer graphics and
OL,9,Fpresenters who were respected
OL,10,Fjournalists.
OL,12,FThe weekend bulletins were short,
OL,13,Fused the remnants of the 1981 generic
OL,14,Fidentity and were denied computer
OL,15,Fgraphics. They were normally
OL,16,Fpresented by Jan Leeming who was
OL,17,Fhugely popular with the public but
OL,18,Fwho was not a journalist ` she was a
OL,19,Fnewsreader in the old BBC sense.
